Carboliq¬Æ GmbH has developed a process for the oiling of mixed and contaminated waste plastics. This allows the hydrocarbons contained in the waste to be regenerated and made available to industry in liquid form for the production of new, high-quality plastics. Avoiding incineration and substituting fossil oil makes a significant contribution to climate protection and resource conservation. As the energy required for the process is supplied exclusively by electrically driven friction mixers, the carboliq¬Æ process can be qualified as a "net-zero technology" when using green electricity. carboliq¬Æ is based in Remscheid. A pilot plant is being operated at the waste disposal center in Ennigerloh. The construction of a first industrial plant is planned at the Chempark Dormagen.

carboliq¬Æ GmbH has developed a process for oiling plastics of different fractions in which the necessary energy is introduced into the process exclusively through mechanical friction. This results in very low energy consumption for chemical recycling processes. With 100% renewable electricity, the process is also completely CO2 -neutral. High yields of more than 80% can be achieved. The petroleum substitute product obtained is a virgin raw material that can be used, for example, to produce new plastic granulates. This can reduce the use of fossil raw materials in the plastics industry. These granulates are also suitable for the production of new, high-performance films that can be used for packaging demanding products with high quality and hygiene requirements
